author: Pip Ellwood-Hughes
title: Ainsley Harriott leaves Strictly Come Dancing 2015
text:
Posted on October 25, 2015 By Pip Ellwood-Hughes Strictly Come Dancing , TV News 
TV chef and presenter Ainsley Harriott became the fourth person to leave Strictly Come Dancing 2015. 
After failing to win over the public, Ainsley and his partner Natalie Lowe found themselves in the bottom two with Jamelia and her partner Tristan MacManus. After both couples danced again it was over to the judges and they all agreed that Ainsley and Natalie were going home. 
Talking about his experience Ainsley said, “It’s been absolutely amazing. I’m sad that it can’t continue but I made a couple of mistakes and the judges are spot on, they know exactly what they are talking about. I’m sad for you Natalie I really am. I wanted to push on a little bit more but it wasn’t meant to be.” 
Natalie added, “I think you are one of the loveliest men I’ve ever met. What you see is what you get with Ainsley. From the people in the street to the judges, everyone speaks so highly of you and you are such a gentleman and you’ve been a dream to work with. I’m sorry we couldn’t go further. We have had a lot of fun in rehearsals.” 
Bryan Adams stopped by to perform during tonight’s results show and a pro group dance kicked things off.
